SIMPLE: rigmarole
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rigmarole
<hw>Rig"ma*role</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[For <ets>ragman
roll</ets>. See <er>Ragman's roll</er>.]</ety> <def>A succession of
confused or nonsensical statements; foolish talk; nonsense.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Often one's dear friend talks something which one scruples to call
<qex>rigmarole</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rigmarole</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rigmarole
<hw>Rig"ma*role</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Consisting of rigmarole;
frivolous; nonsensical; foolish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rigol</ent>⟦br⟧
